To create an agent specifically for function calling in this system, you can follow the example provided in the documentation. Here’s how:

1. Use the `client.beta.agents.create()` method (TypeScript) or the equivalent `curl` request.
2. Specify the `model`, `name`, `description`, and `tools` (including the function definition) in the request payload.

### Example (TypeScript):
```typescript
let agent = await client.beta.agents.create({
    model: "mistral-medium-2505",
    description: "Your agent's description",
    name: "your-agent-name",
    tools: [
        {
            type: "function",
            function: {
                name: "yourFunctionName",
                description: "Description of what the function does",
                parameters: {
                    type: "object",
                    properties: {
                        // Define required parameters here
                    },
                    required: ["parameter1", "parameter2"] // List required parameters
                },
            },
        },
    ],
});
```
**Source:** [Section 3, Function Calling (TypeScript example)](from platform-docs-public/public/agents/tools/function_calling.md).

### Example (cURL):
```bash
curl --location "https://api.mistral.ai/v1/agents" \
     --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
     --header 'Accept: application/json' \
     --header "Authorization: Bearer $MISTRAL_API_KEY" \
     --data '{
     "model": "mistral-medium-2505",
     "name": "your-agent-name",
     "description": "Your agent'\''s description",
     "tools": [
         {
             "function": {
                 "name": "your_function_name",
                 "parameters": {
                     "type": "object",
                     "properties": {
                         // Define required parameters here
                     },
                     "required": ["parameter1"]
                 },
                 "description": "Description of what the function does."
             }
         }
     ]
}'
```
**Source:** [Section 3, Function Calling (cURL example)](from platform-docs-public/public/agents/tools/function_calling.md).

The output will be an **agent object containing the agent ID**, which you can use to start a conversation.
**Source:** [Section 2, Function Calling](from platform-docs-public/public/agents/tools/function_calling.md).
